This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with generating coherent and reasonable story endings through understanding context clues and applying commonsense knowledge. It also involves attention mechanisms and encoding schemes, which are common techniques used in NLP. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR) as these fields are closely related to NLP and often overlap in research topics and techniques.
